1. Ne volim da jedem u *prljavoj* kuhinji. (I don't like to eat in a *dirty* kitchen.)
2. Moramo da operemo *prljave* tanjire pre nego što ih stavimo u mašinu za pranje sudova. (We have to wash the *dirty* plates before putting them in the dishwasher.)
3. Oni žive u *prljavom* kvartu, ali se ne žele preseliti. (They live in a *dirty* neighborhood, but they don't want to move.)
4. Tvoje ruke su *prljave*, moraš da ih opereš pre večere. (Your hands are *dirty*, you need to wash them before dinner.)
5. *Prljavi* veš ne bi trebalo da ostaviš dugo u korpi za veš. (You shouldn't leave *dirty* laundry in the basket for too long.)
6. Njegov auto je bio *prljav* nakon dugog putovanja. (His car was *dirty* after a long trip.)
7. Ova ulica je uvek *prljava* jer grad ne održava čistoću. (This street is always *dirty* because the city doesn't keep it clean.)
8. Da li si ikada jeo u ovom restoranu? Ne, čuo sam da je *prljav*. (Have you ever eaten at this restaurant? No, I heard it's *dirty*.)
9. Kupio je novu mašinu za pranje veša jer mu stara nije dobro prala *prljave* stvari. (He bought a new washing machine because his old one didn't wash *dirty* clothes well.)
10. Uvek obrišem *prljavu* površinu pre nego što je očistim sredstvom. (I always wipe off a *dirty* surface before cleaning it with a cleaner.)